The Herald Tendai Rupapa,Senior Reporter The First Lady Auxillia Mnangagwa, in conjunction with the Traffic Safety Council of Zimbabwe and the Zimbabwe Republic Police today began a road safety awareness campaign in the run-up to the festive season.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463738 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Road traffic accidents claim hundreds of lives and leave hundreds more injured during the festive season annually. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-463741 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/f62103b7-1fa9-4396-b9f4-fb41e57b5826-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />Her first port of call was at the Harare South tollgate on the Harare-Masvingo highway.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463736 size-article-featured-image" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/730da1ac-6760-4322-8768-50acb0c85585-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/730da1ac-6760-4322-8768-50acb0c85585-680x380.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/730da1ac-6760-4322-8768-50acb0c85585-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />Amai Mnangagwa is engaging drivers, conductors and travellers stressing the need to observe safety.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463747 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/04a33c8f-65f5-4ac9-a16a-73ad5b66bbe6.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/04a33c8f-65f5-4ac9-a16a-73ad5b66bbe6.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/04a33c8f-65f5-4ac9-a16a-73ad5b66bbe6-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />She is scheduled to visit several tollgates engaging transporters and drivers about safety and sharing hints with them on how to reduce road carnage.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463762 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/e27267c0-da6b-43b8-8494-7cd7707c0f28.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/e27267c0-da6b-43b8-8494-7cd7707c0f28.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/e27267c0-da6b-43b8-8494-7cd7707c0f28-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />Road users have welcomed the initiative by the First Lady.